  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nGo 1.16 is the support for embedding files and folders into the application binary at compile-time without using a third-party package.\r\n\r\nNow go-ethereum has been built with Go 1.17, however it still relies on third-party packages(https://github.com/go-bindata/go-bindata) to embed static assets in Go binaries:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/v1.10.9/cmd/faucet/faucet.go#L20 \r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/v1.10.9/signer/fourbyte/fourbyte.go#L17\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/v1.10.9/internal/jsre/deps/deps.go#L20\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/v1.10.9/signer/rules/deps/deps.go#L20\r\n\r\nBy using embed package instead of go-bindata, we will not require an extra step to add/update assets every time they change and will reduce external dependencies.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nDo you have ideas regarding the implementation of this feature?\r\nuse embed package instead of go-bindata,\r\nAre you willing to implement this feature?\r\nYes, I would be glad to do it.",
